name: The World will be Ours"
description:
"I seek for your presences for a hundred cycles. All kinds of beings I have meet are a silent witness, all things that passing by at my journey have been my travel knowledge.
But yours, indeed, far more superior. The solitude that covers your surroundings is a teacher of your everyday meditation. That, I need most; your perspective, your godly nexus...to face my unforeseen challenge yet. To uncover what I desire most about you.

And now the world will be ours."

Valentine 2022 drop. 
Ink and Pencil on Moleskine 185gr. Digital on Photoshop. PNG. 3510x5828. 2016-2022
